Ask HN: Submissions Don't Seem to Exist
text:
Except for me if I'm logged in.

https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=32697281

https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=32697432

If I'm logged out and follow the above links, a blank HN page appears.

If I'm logged in, I can see the submissions (by following the links and in the 'New' section), but they do not display a comment box and the entry in the 'New' section does not contain a 'discuss' link.

If there's something in those submissions which are inappropriate (one is a link to an article about malware using golang, and the other is an Ask HN wondering why the former isn't allowed to have comments), I can't see what it is.

If there's something inappropriate in them, I apologize and will delete them, but that seems unlikely.

Any thoughts or suggestions would be greatly appreciated.
